The paper deals with provenance tracking in data-centric systems, which is a core concern in database systems (cs.DB). The paper presents a calculus for modeling data updates, which is related to logic and computation (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the operational semantics of the calculus, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
